unarticulated until a later period.Focusing on England and France during the Hundred Years War, Crane draws on wardrobe accounts, manuscript illuminations, chronicles, archaeological evidence, and literature to recover the material as well as the verbal constructions of identity. She seeks intersections between theories of practice and performance that explain how appearances and language connect when courtiers dress as wild men to interrupt a wedding feast, when knights choose crests and badges to supplement their coats of arms, and when Joan of Arc cross-dresses for the court of inquisition after her capture.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aCostumexMedieval. 0aCostumezFrancexHistoryxMedievald500-1500. 0aCostumezGreat BritainxHistoryxMedievald500-1500. 0aHundred Years' Ward339-1453xSocial aspectszFrance. 0aHundred Years' Ward339-1453xSocial aspectszGreat Britain. 0aHundred Years' War, 1339-1453xSocial aspectszFrance. 0aHundred Years' War, 1339-1453xSocial aspectszGreat Britain. 0aIdentity (Psychology)zFrancexHistoryxTo 1500. 0aIdentity (Psychology)zGreat BritainxHistoryxTo 1500. 0aIdentity (Psychology)zGreat BritainxHistoryyTo 1500. 0aRitualzFrancexHistoryxTo 1500. 0aRitualzGreat BritainxHistoryxTo 1500. 0aRitualzGreat BritainxHistoryyTo 1500. 4aLiterature. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Medieval.2bisacsh  aCultural Studies.  aLiterature.  aMedieval and Renaissance Studies.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPenn Press eBook Package Complete Collectionz978311041345808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPenn Press eBook-Package Literaturez978311041354008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Pennsylvania Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311045954840uhttps://doi.org/10.9783/978081220170340uhttps://ww